{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"New Design!","content":"<html><head></head><body><p>Just today I launched the new design of my blog. I had been upset over my old design for a while; I couldn&#x2019;t really put my finger on why, but I just felt that the design was really messy and unprofessional. One of things that REALLY bugged me is that the colours looked awful on Windows machines. For the new design, I decided to play it safe and stick with mostly grayscale colours. </p>\n<p><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 588px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 64.28571428571428%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-667\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"old_design\" title=\"old_design\" src=\"/static/c7082a9c4fcd78b80b09695d47c5f48f/4214e/old_design.png\" srcset=\"/static/c7082a9c4fcd78b80b09695d47c5f48f/19bd1/old_design.png 163w,\n/static/c7082a9c4fcd78b80b09695d47c5f48f/d3bcb/old_design.png 325w,\n/static/c7082a9c4fcd78b80b09695d47c5f48f/4214e/old_design.png 588w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 588px) 100vw, 588px\">\n  </span></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">The old design&#x2026;ew!!</div>\n<p>I grabbed the background pattern that I created last year, and used it as a foundation of the new design. I didn&#x2019;t want it to be too distracting so I toned down its opacity quite a bit. I&#x2019;d like to work on a new background sometime soon because I feel this one is a bit too disorganized.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 450px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-681\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"repeat_Bg\" title=\"repeat_Bg\" src=\"/static/ce8587a4bc1e6840438ea38ab4b8d7cc/df2c7/repeat_Bg.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/ce8587a4bc1e6840438ea38ab4b8d7cc/aca85/repeat_Bg.jpg 163w,\n/static/ce8587a4bc1e6840438ea38ab4b8d7cc/0954f/repeat_Bg.jpg 325w,\n/static/ce8587a4bc1e6840438ea38ab4b8d7cc/df2c7/repeat_Bg.jpg 450w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px\">\n  </span>\n</p>\n<div class=\"sub\">My repeatable background pattern</div>\n<p>I went through various variations of the design, getting feedback from friends and coworkers. <a href=\"http://markdunkley.com/\">Mark Dunkley</a> gave me a lot of quality feedback, as usual. I really liked the idea of having a 100% width &lt;div&gt;&#x2019;s for the headers and footers. Later on I felt that having multiple &lt;div&gt;&#x2019;s spanning across the page was a bit overkill, so I decided to keep it for just the footer.</p>\n<p>Big props to Steve Hatcher&#x2019;s <a href=\"http://www.cssstickyfooter.com/\" title=\"CSS Sticky Footer\" target=\"_blank\">CSS Sticky Footer</a>, which I&#x2019;m using using for this site. I can&#x2019;t even think of how much time I would have spent if I were to figure out how to make a sticky footer on my own. Thank you, Mr. Hatcher!!</p>\n<p><img src=\"http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/old_design2.png\" alt=\"old_design2\" title=\"old_design2\" width=\"588\" height=\"378\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-687\"></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">An earlier version of the new design</div>\n<p>I think now I can finally say that I&#x2019;m content with the design of my blog. Any feedback/comments would be greatly appreciated! I also have a pretty kick-ass Shopify tutorial coming up, so stay tuned!</p>\n<p><strong>UPDATE (11/20/2009):</strong> Taking Caroline&#x2019;s advice, I decided to make it so that my logo is only present on the index page. This should make it easier for visitors with smaller laptops to browse my site :). Also, created a <a href=\"http://blog.tetsutakara.com/asdfasfda\">404 page.</a></p>\n</body></html>"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"new-design"}}